    "explanation": "## Unified Fix for Agreed Findings\n\n### Critical Issues Fixed:\n\n**1. Mandatory Dependencies → Optional Extras** (`pyproject.toml`)\n   - **Issue**: FastAPI/uvicorn were added to main `dependencies`, bloating CLI-only installations by ~5 transitive dependencies\n   - **Fix**: Moved to `[project.optional-dependencies]` under `server` extra. Users install via: `pip install silverpond-factory[server]`\n   - **Consensus**: Moving optional features to extras is Python packaging best practice (PEP 508)\n\n**2. Return Type Annotation Missing** (`factory/server.py`)\n   - **Issue**: `hello()` lacked return type, reducing type safety and IDE support\n   - **Fix**: Introduced Pydantic `HelloResponse` model with `message: str` field. Endpoint returns `HelloResponse` with explicit `-> HelloResponse` annotation. Improves auto-documentation and runtime validation.\n\n**3. Module-Level App Instantiation Side Effects** (`factory/server.py`)\n   - **Issue**: `app = FastAPI()` at module level creates side effects on import\n   - **Fix**: Introduced `create_app()` factory function for lazy initialization. Module now imports cleanly without instantiating the app object prematurely.\n\n**4. Missing Structured Logging** (`factory/cli.py`)\n   - **Issue**: Used `typer.echo()` instead of `logging` module, preventing structured log filtering and level control\n   - **Fix**: Added `logging.basicConfig()` with ISO timestamp format. Replaced echo calls with `logger.info()`/`logger.error()`. Info/error messages now respect logging levels.\n\n**5. Host Parameter Not Validated** (`factory/cli.py`)\n   - **Issue**: Users could pass `--host ';;;;'` or `--host 256.256.256.256` with no validation feedback\n   - **Fix**: Added `_validate_host()` using `ipaddress` module + regex for hostnames. Raises `typer.BadParameter` at parse time (not at uvicorn startup).\n\n**6. Port Parameter Not Bounded** (`factory/cli.py`)\n   - **Issue**: Invalid ports (< 1, > 65535) would silently fail at runtime\n   - **Fix**: Added `_validate_port()` enforcing 1–65535 range. Raises `typer.BadParameter` immediately on invalid input.\n\n**7. Blocking Server Prevents Concurrent Operations** (`factory/cli.py`)\n   - **Issue**: `uvicorn.run()` blocks indefinitely; no graceful shutdown or signal handling\n   - **Fix**: Added `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` handlers that log shutdown and exit cleanly. Wrapped `uvicorn.run()` in try/except to catch `OSError` (e.g., port in use) with clear error messages.\n\n**8. Zero HTTP Test Coverage** (`tests/test_server.py`)\n   - **Issue**: `/hello` endpoint untested; single point of failure\n   - **Fix**: Created `tests/test_server.py` with FastAPI `TestClient` fixture. Tests cover:\n     - 200 status code\n     - Correct response JSON\n     - Pydantic model validation\n     - 404 on invalid endpoints\n\n### Architecture Improvements:\n\n- **Lazy app initialization**: Prevents multiple app instances if `factory.server` is imported in tests or other modules\n- **Pydantic response models**: Enables OpenAPI schema documentation automatically via FastAPI\n- **Signal handlers**: Graceful shutdown on `Ctrl+C` or container termination\n- **Early validation**: CLI argument errors reported at parse time, not at server startup\n- **Logging framework**: Operational events (startup, shutdown, errors) now visible to operators with consistent formatting\n\n### Backward Compatibility:\n\n- `factory serve` command works identically (same defaults and options)\n- Existing code importing `factory.server` continues to work\n- No breaking changes to CLI interface or API contracts",
